Package org.neo4j.kernel.impl.index.schema

Class GenericIndexKeyValidator

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.neo4j.kernel.impl.index.schema.GenericIndexKeyValidator
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IndexValueValidator
    class GenericIndexKeyValidator
extends Object
implements IndexValueValidator
    Validates Value[] tuples, whether or not they fit inside a GBPTree with a layout using CompositeGenericKey. Most values won't even be serialized to CompositeGenericKey, values that fit well within the margin.

      • worstCaseLength

        private static int worstCaseLength​(Value[] values)
        A method for calculating some sort of worst-case length of a value tuple. This have to be a cheap call and can return false positives. It exists to avoid serializing all value tuples into native keys, which can be expensive.
        Parameters:
        values - the value tuple to calculate some exaggerated worst-case size of.
        Returns:
        the calculated worst-case size of the value tuple.
